p\">Handles.cpp</a>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>We sometimes see SIGSEGV on exit when the handles are destructed</li>\n<li>They don't work on non-default streams</li>\n</ol>\n<p>We tried making the handles table thread-local, but that causes slow downs and deadlocks because the handles can be destructed after every forward pass in a data parallel module.</p>\n<p>We should figure out a better solution.</p>", "body_text": "There are two problems with the way we manage cudnnHandles in Handles.cpp:\n\nWe sometimes see SIGSEGV on exit when the handles are destructed\nThey don't work on non-default streams\n\nWe tried making the handles table thread-local, but that causes slow downs and deadlocks because the handles can be destructed after every forward pass in a data parallel module.\nWe should figure out a better solution.", "body": "There are two problems with the way we manage cudnnHandles in [Handles.cpp](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/torch/csrc/cudnn/Handles.cpp):\r\n\r\n1. We sometimes see SIGSEGV on exit when the handles are destructed\r\n2. They don't work on non-default streams\r\n\r\nWe tried making the handles table thread-local, but that causes slow downs and deadlocks because the handles can be destructed after every forward pass in a data parallel module.\r\n\r\nWe should figure out a better solution."}